description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/routing/dtn.c
Lines: 28-45

In find_oldest():

    static int find_oldest(const struct lichen_dtn_buffer *buf)
    {
        int oldest_idx = -1;
        uint32_t oldest_time = UINT32_MAX;

        for (int i = 0; i < CONFIG_LICHEN_DTN_MAX_MESSAGES; i++) {
            if (buf->messages[i].valid) {
                /* Wraparound-safe: we just compare raw values. */
                if (buf->messages[i].buffered_at_ms < oldest_time) {
                    oldest_time = buf->messages[i].buffered_at_ms;
                    oldest_idx = i;
                }
            }
        }
        return oldest_idx;
    }

The comment claims 'wraparound-safe' but the comparison 'buffered_at_ms < oldest_time' is NOT wraparound-safe. After ~49 days of uptime, the millisecond counter wraps.

Consider: oldest_time = 0xFFFFFF00 (old), buffered_at_ms = 0x00000100 (wrapped, actually newer). The comparison 0x100 < 0xFFFFFF00 is TRUE, so the newer message is incorrectly identified as older.

The correct wraparound-safe approach uses signed comparison like:
    (int32_t)(buffered_at_ms - oldest_time) < 0

This is used correctly elsewhere in the codebase (e.g., router.c line 282, gradient.c line 98) but not here.
